===Chebyshev&#x27;s inequality===

An observation is rarely more than a few standard deviations away from the mean. Chebyshev&#x27;s inequality ensures that, for all distributions for which the standard deviation is defined, the amount of data within a number of standard deviations of the mean is at least as much as given in the following table.

